            <fr:title text="Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem">Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_k : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [-\infty , +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> be a sequence of measurable functions. Suppose that</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>There exists a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0057.xml" addr="FA-0057" title="Measurable function">measurable function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [-\infty , +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n \to  f]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0049.xml" addr="FA-0049" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>There exists a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0058.xml" addr="FA-0058" title="Summable">summable</fr:link> function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [-\infty , +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f_n(x)| \leq  g(x)]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> and for <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0049.xml" addr="FA-0049" title="Almost everywhere">almost every</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol>
            <fr:p>Then,</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\int  f(x)dx = \lim _{n \to  +\infty } \int  f_n(x)dx}]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>243</fr:anchor>
